-- Plane Crash in Islamabad Hills Killed All 152 People on Board, Malik Says
-- Khurrum Anis
-- 2010-07-28T10:55:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/plane-crash-in-islamabad-hills-killed-all-152-people-on-board-malik-says.html

          
          
             There were no survivors from the
plane crash in Pakistan, Interior Minister Rehman Malik said on
television. All 152 people, including 8 crew members, were
killed, he said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Khurrum Anis in Karachi at 
 kkhan14@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     A Pakistani man checks the lists of the passengers killed in a plane crash in The Margala Hills on the outskirts of Islamabad. Photographer: Asif Hassan/AFP/Getty Images  
                           

     
